## Context

- pten-loss-pancancer-dependency-atlas: Advanced from `planning` → `development`. Broke plan into 5 developer tasks following established atlas pattern.
- Developer tasks created: #463 (Phase 1 classifier, P5), #464 (Phase 2 PI3K/AKT effect sizes, P4), #465 (Phase 3 genome-wide screen, P3), #467 (Phase 4 PRISM drugs, P3), #468 (Phase 5 TCGA clinical, P2)
- RD addendum incorporated: ICMT, CHD1, PNKP, SMARCA4, BCL-XL, ATM, TTK, RAD51 as priority targets in Phase 3 (tasks #432, #445 closed)
- Key design: PTEN-lost = deep deletion OR truncating mutation (differs from CDKN2A/MTAP). Missense VUS excluded. Expression cross-validation required.
- PIK3CB is the positive control (ROBUST in ≥2 cancer types = success criterion)
- Next: Developer executes Phase 1 first (all other phases depend on classifier output). Monitor for Phase 1 completion → advance pipeline.
- Journal #851 documents all decisions.
